15 Mar 2018 04:26






Absolutely stellar. I can't imagine how much work went into this, but it certainly paid off. +1

That said, I noticed some typos here and there, but I have no idea how to go about fixing them.

Onethough.

–block


When you end a piece of dialogue with a period, the following word should be capitalized. If the following words form a dependent clause, the dialogue should end with a comma.

So, this is correct:



 The speed at which she speaks — as well as the fact that she's stood at your door in the first place — reveals her lie.
附加记录：    

But here




附加记录：    

The period after  is technically part of the same sentence. The corrected form would thus read:




附加记录：    










